      <front>
         <p>Date?: to Harding<note xml:id="ftn2-337" place="foot" n="337">ATL MS-Copy-Micro-0485-1.</note>
         </p>
      </front>
      <body>
         <p rend="end">Tuesday 15<hi rend="sup">th</hi>.</p>
         <p>Mr Harding</p>
         <p>Dr Sir—In sending out the Mao. H.Bk. I bought at your shop yesty.—I found, the fore-edges <hi rend="italic">not</hi> cut through, so I had to do that—well knowing the impossibility of a poor Maori being able to do it. And so I have thought to write a line to you about it: you can very well take off ¼ in. more.—And, if you have more to bind or cut, leave <hi rend="italic">½ in. more at tail.</hi>
         </p>
         <p>                             Yours truly</p>
         <p>                                                     W. Colenso.</p>
      </body>
  </text>
